==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*skrīban'', from Latin [[scribere]] ‘write’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[skriva|skrīva]], Old Saxon [[skriƀan|skrīƀan]] (Dutch [[schrijven]]), Old High German [[scriban|scrīban]] (German [[schreiben]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈʃri:van/}}

===Verb===
{{Unicode|'''scrīfan'''}} (class I strong: ''3 singular present'' {{Unicode|'''[[scrifeþ|scrīfeþ]]'''}}, ''3 singular preterite'' {{Unicode|'''[[scraf|scrāf]]'''}}, ''preterite plural'' '''[[scrifon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[scrifen]]''')
# to [[decree]], [[appoint]]
# to pass judgement, [[ordain]], [[prescribe]]

